@(#)README 1.1 92/07/30 SMI

Notes on fixed width fonts:

- The nominal point size of each font is based on the distance in pixels
  from the top of the 'T' to the bottom of the 'y'.

- The "serif" fonts are loosely based on Prestige typewriter; "cour"
  fonts are Courier.  The "screen" fonts have been tuned for the Sun screen.

- Some fonts had different names before release 2.0; there are symbolic
  links between the old font names and the new ones.

- All fonts except the small sized ones have been extended to display
  ISO Latin 1 (ISO 8859/1) characters. These bitmaps are displayed when
  the font is addressed by an 8-bit single byte character. 


